verses.roman:
rājaputa-jāti muñi, o-pāre mora ghara
mora icchā haya--'haṅa vaiṣṇava-kiṅkara'

synonyms: rājaputa-jāti—belong to the Rājaputa caste; muñi—I; o-pāre—on the other side of the Yamunā; mora ghara—my residence; mora icchā haya—I wish; haṅa—to become; vaiṣṇava-kiṅkara—the servant of a Vaiṣṇava.
translation: "I belong to the Rājaputa caste, and my home is just on the other side of the River Yamunā. However, I wish to be the servant of a Vaiṣṇava.
